Module 1: What is a Company in Odoo? (Detailed Explanation)
🎯 Module Objective

In this module, you will learn what a Company is in Odoo, why it is required, and how Odoo uses company information in daily business operations.

1. What is a Company?

A Company in Odoo is a legal business organization that uses Odoo to manage its business processes.

Think of a company as the owner of all business activities inside Odoo.

For example, if your business name is:

Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd

then all your business transactions—such as sales, purchases, inventory, accounting, and employees—belong to this company.

Real-World Example

Imagine you start a software company called Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd.

Your company:

Develops software applications
Sells software products
Purchases computers and servers
Pays employee salaries
Pays GST to the government
Generates invoices for customers

Instead of managing all these tasks manually, you use Odoo ERP.

Here, Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd becomes your Company in Odoo.

2. Why Does Odoo Need Company Information?

Every business document created in Odoo needs company details.

For example, when you create:

Sales Quotation
Sales Order
Customer Invoice
Purchase Order
Delivery Slip
Accounting Report

Odoo automatically prints your company information on these documents.

Example Invoice
-----------------------------------------
Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd
No.125, OMR Road
Chennai - 600096
Tamil Nadu, India

Invoice No : INV00015
Customer : ABC Solutions
Date : 15-07-2026

Amount : ₹45,000
GST : ₹8,100

Total : ₹53,100
-----------------------------------------

Without company information, the invoice would not contain your business identity.

3. What Information Does a Company Store?

Every company stores basic business information.

