4. Company vs Database

This is one of the most important concepts in Odoo.

Many beginners think a Company and a Database are the same, but they are different.

Database

A Database stores all the information in Odoo.

It contains:

Companies
Users
Customers
Products
Sales
Purchases
Inventory
Accounting

Think of the database as a container.

Company

A Company is one business inside that database.

One database can manage multiple companies.

Example
Odoo Database
│
├── Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd
│     ├── Sales
│     ├── Purchase
│     ├── Inventory
│     └── Accounting
│
├── Ravinder Retail Pvt Ltd
│     ├── Sales
│     ├── Purchase
│     └── Inventory
│
└── Ravinder Logistics Pvt Ltd

Here:

There is one database.
Inside it are three different companies.
Each company has its own business data.
5. Company Logo

A company logo represents the company's brand.

It appears on:

Quotations
Sales Orders
Purchase Orders
Invoices
Delivery Orders
PDF Reports

Example:

      [Company Logo]

Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd

A logo makes business documents look professional.

6. Company Address

The address tells customers where the business is located.

Example:

Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd
No.125, OMR Road
Chennai – 600096
Tamil Nadu
India

This address is printed on all official documents.

7. Currency

The company currency determines how money is displayed.

For example:

| Country | Currency |
| ------- | -------- |
| India   | INR (₹)  |
| USA     | USD ($)  |
| UK      | GBP (£)  |
| UAE     | AED      |

Example:

Laptop Price

₹75,000

If the company is in the USA, Odoo displays:

$950

===

8. Time Zone

The time zone ensures that all activities are recorded with the correct local time.

For Ravinder Technologies Pvt Ltd, the time zone is:

Asia/Kolkata

This affects:

Sales Order Date
Invoice Date
Employee Attendance
Meeting Schedule
Activity Logs
9. Language

The language setting changes the interface and reports.

Supported languages include:

English
Tamil
Hindi
French
German
Spanish

Example:

If the language is English, menus appear in English.

If the language is French, the interface changes to French (if installed).

10. Tax Information

Tax information helps Odoo calculate taxes automatically.

Examples:

GST (India)
VAT (Europe)
Sales Tax (USA)

When creating an invoice, Odoo automatically calculates the tax based on the company's tax configuration.

11. Benefits of Configuring a Company

A properly configured company helps you:

Create professional business documents.
Maintain accurate accounting records.
Calculate taxes correctly.
Display your company branding.
Comply with local regulations.
Manage business operations efficiently.
